# BreakingBricksNews mixes source/text (scripts, docs, generated stories) with a
# handful of binary brand assets. The repo-root catch-all
#   marketing/** filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# is right for the all-binary marketing subtrees (ItalianJob, YakYakOriginals)
# but wrong here: it would push every .md / .py / .sh / .json into Git LFS, so a
# fresh clone without git-lfs reads pointers instead of source and nothing diffs.
#
# This file overrides the catch-all for THIS subtree only:
#   - text/source  -> normal Git (diffable, 3-way merge, EOL normalized). The
#                     `-filter` clears the inherited `filter=lfs` so blobs are
#                     stored inline, not as LFS pointers.
#   - binary assets -> stay in LFS (re-stated explicitly so they survive even if
#                     the root catch-all is ever narrowed).
# Do NOT use `-diff`/`-merge` on the text rules — that would flag them binary.

# --- text / source: keep OUT of LFS, keep diffable -------------------------
*.md           text diff merge -filter
*.sh           text diff merge -filter
*.py           text diff merge -filter
*.js           text diff merge -filter
*.json         text diff merge -filter
*.txt          text diff merge -filter
*.env          text diff merge -filter
# Keep attributes files themselves as plain text (else marketing/** would LFS
# them and a no-lfs clone would read a pointer instead of these rules).
.gitattributes text diff merge -filter
.gitkeep       text diff merge -filter

# --- binary assets: keep IN LFS --------------------------------------------
*.mp3 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.jpg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.jpeg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.gif filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.mp4 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.mov filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.wav filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.pdf filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.zip filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
